This spontaneous report was received from a consumer (patient's mother) and concerns a 4-month-old female 
patient from the United States: 017536280A.
The patient's weight was 12 pounds while the height and medical history was not reported.
The patient was treated with paracetamol (suspension, oral) 2.5 ml once, initiated on 17-FEB-2016 for an 
unspecified indication. Concomitant medications were not reported.
On 17-FEB-2016, the mother grabbed the wrong bottle and gave the patient the children's instead of the infant's 
paracetamol (accidental wrong drug administration). 
Action taken with paracetamol was not reported.
